Roles & directory structure вЂ” Must

What is a Role?

Roles = Way to organize playbook into reusable, structured components.

Simple analogy:

Playbook = entire recipe book
Role     = one recipe (nginx, mysql, java)

Role directory structure:

roles/
в””в”Ђв”Ђ nginx/                    # role name
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ tasks/
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ main.yml          # main tasks
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ handlers/
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ main.yml          # handlers
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ vars/
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ main.yml          # variables
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ defaults/
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ main.yml          # default variables (lowest priority)
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ templates/
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ nginx.conf.j2     # jinja2 templates
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ files/
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ nginx.conf        # static files
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ meta/
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ main.yml          # role dependencies
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ README.md

Each file does:

| Folder              | Purpose                                   |
|---------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| tasks/main.yml      | Main tasks to execute                     |
| handlers/main.yml   | Handlers (notify triggers)                |
| vars/main.yml       | Role variables (high priority)            |
| defaults/main.yml   | Default variables (low priority, overridable) |
| templates/          | Jinja2 template files (.j2)               |
| files/              | Static files to copy                      |
| meta/main.yml       | Role dependencies                         |


